<TEXT>
up with people celebrated its 25th anniversary 
thursday with a parade of brightly colored flags and performers 
and pledges the wholesome troubadors will continue to sing their 
upbeat songs for peace 
about 5000 people attended the opening ceremonies at the 
colorado convention center to commemorate the founding of the group 
former astronaut eugene cernan the last man to walk on the moon 
and a member of up with peoples board of directors gave the 
opening remarks 
we are here to celebrate not only the dream that has brought 
us together but you the dream that has become up with people 
cernan said i havent been this high since ive been on the 
moon 
the events honorary chairman president bush sent a 
congratulatory message as did canadian prime minister brian 
mulroney west german chancellor helmut kohl and pope john paul ii 
j blanton belk a former navy officer started the 
multinational musical goodwill troupe in 1965 to promote an upbeat 
message of brotherhood at a time when much youthful energy in the 
united states went into civil rights marches and antiwar protests 
people from 41 countries and every state are attending the 
anniversary celebration which includes concerts and slide shows 
more than 12000 people have participated in yearlong stints 
singing with the tucson arizbased nonprofit group 
belk 65 told the groups alumni to keep spreading the ideals 
of the program in their daily lives 
give more than you think you can give without any fear 
because you are the true spirit of hope he said 
speakers at a forum friday to discuss global concerns such as 
the environment and political cooperation will include belgian 
prime minister wilfried martens dr shoichiro toyoda president of 
the toyota motor company and mexicos oscarwinning filmmaker 
manuel orango 
others attending include princess margriet of the netherlands 
and soviet journalist vladimir pozner 
