a federal probe of mayor david dinkins sale of 
stock to his son has ended without any charges being filed the 
government announced thursday 
the stock transfer was brought to light last year during 
democrat dinkins campaign against former manhattan us attorney 
rudolph giuliani 
dinkins sold 588 shares of stock in inner city cable 
broadcasting co to his son david jr in october 1985 for 
58000 three years earlier he had listed its value at over 1 
million on a financial disclosure form 
us attorney andrew maloney in brooklyn investigated the 
transfer of the stock apparently to see whether it was authentic 
and whether the proper amount of taxes was paid on it 
maloney said the investigation has been completed without the 
filing of criminal charges 
dinkins said of maloneys finding his conclusion speaks for 
itself 
maloney said the results of the investigation have been sent to 
the city department of investigations at the departments request 
the department is probing whether dinkins properly filed city 
financial disclosure forms on the stock transfer also being 
investigated is whether he violated any conflict of interest laws 
by voting as manhattan borough president in 1987 in favor of a 
zoning change for inner city and in june 1989 concerning a transfer 
of a cable franchise to a related company 
of the city probe dinkins said i look forward to a speedy 
resolution of the similar inquiry being conducted by the department 
of investigation 
he added in a written statement until that time i will have 
no further comment 
</TEXT>
