<TEXT>
designer claude montana of the lanvin fashion house 
won the coveted golden thimble prize thursday to wrap up five days 
of haute couture winter collection shows 
montana won the prize the french capitals top fashion award 
with 24 votes cast by a jury of journalists second place went to 
the balmain house with nine votes 
it made a sweet revenge for montana whose first couture show 
for lanvin last winter was widely deemed a flop but this time he 
was highly praised for a stronglystructured luxury collection 
shows at the opposite end of the spectrum by hubert de givenchy 
and per spook preceded the vote givenchy showed his talents as a 
master of opulent sophistication while spook took a lighthearted 
more casual approach 
givenchy presented a big collection dedicated to the people 
behind the scenes especially to his head couture assistant 
gilberte thomassin she has been with givenchy since he left 
balenciaga and founded his house about 30 years ago 
the craftsmanship of true couture was evident in a collection of 
beautifully constructed suits dresses and evening wear 
the silhouette was firmly givenchy with wide shoulders over 
slim hips and skirts at wearable length just above the knee 
new details included rounded collars cut away to reveal little 
ascotlike ties on superb silk blouses 
as usual givenchy loved the look of suede in shades like royal 
blue and brown this time he added fillips of python trim a 
favorite with yves saintlaurent as well 
woodchuck trim or white mink sleeves on a dressy black suit 
added surprisingly elegant touches to handsome day wear 
skirt suits in chine or flecked tweed were also big but 
givenchy also threw in straight slim trousers and a few belted day 
dresses in fall shades of autumnleaf yellow or red spruce green 
and brick plus a dash of powder blue raspberry or plum 
he didnt stint on his evening wear featuring asymmetrical 
shimmering lame cocktail dresses with lowered hems at the back to 
fabulous ball gowns 
here is where one can see the skill of backroom artisans not 
only in seamless sewing but in dazzling decor the iridescent 
failles endless patterns of pearls jet beads sparkling mirror 
sequins and other embroidery 
norwegianborn per spook went back to his roots for inspiration 
he laid on a lively winter carnival full of norwegian jacquard 
knits mixed up in duffel coats minis leggings and boots and 
even topping them with stocking caps right out of santas workshop 
a few quilted jackets and crepe de chine gowns were amusingly 
printed with lighthearted spook fashion sketches 
while spook didnt invest in many elaborate evening clothes he 
did show one of the prettiest bridal gowns in town a charming 
fullskirted taffeta confection sprigged with pink forgetmenots 
worn by his newlyarrived russian model masha suvorova 
late wednesday valentino put on a show of elaborate ensembles 
that got to be so pretty they nearly became too much of a good 
thing like an overdose of chocolates 
valentino said he was inspired by artisans work like prismatic 
crystal or the inlays of a fancy l8thcentury cabinetmaker 
the results were often stunning tours de force as in the 
kaleidoscopic satin short evening gown in shades of sapphire 
emerald and peacock blue 
he showed a breathtaking long gown with a multicolored mosaic 
top over a maypoleribbon basque waist flaring into a luminous 
cloud of chiffon in deep turquoise green and siena 
