<TEXT>
president fidel castro told a huge rally thursday 
night that president bush has a sick obsession with trying to 
topple his communist government 
neither asleep nor awake can bush forget about cuba castro 
told hundreds of thousands of people massed in revolutionary plaza 
to mark the 37th anniversary of the birth of his movement that took 
power in 1959 
smiling he invited americans to send boats to pick up cubans 
wishing to leave the country his comment came after dozens of 
cubans sought asylum in foreign embassies in recent weeks 
if the yankees decide that they want to receive these poor 
persecuted citizens let them send the boats and the visas he 
said with sarcastic intonation 
it was not clear whether castro was suggesting a renewal of the 
mariel boatlift under that operation 125000 cubans went to 
florida during a fivemonth period in 1980 
despite deepening economic problems and growing international 
isolation castro was on the offensive for most of his twohour 
45minute speech cuban flags adorned buildings and citizens were 
urged by state media to attend the event and the anniversary is a 
national holiday 
castro escalated a dispute with spain he renounced a 25 
million economic cooperation program that spanish authorities 
suspended last week in a conflict with cuba over 18 asylumseekers 
at the spanish embassy in this capital 
the cuban president invited spain and the european community to 
open an office in havana to process applications for cubans who 
wish to emigrate embassies he said should not be used as 
travel agencies 
spain has refused to expel the cubans cuba says they should not 
have been given refuge because they are not being sought by cuban 
authorities the incident has produced harsh public exchanges 
between the two countries 
the cuban president blamed the embassy crisis here on the united 
states according to official news agency reports monitored in 
mexico city dozens of cubans have sought asylum in various foreign 
missions recently 
castro said no cuban who enters an embassy by force will be be 
granted permission to leave the country the official cuban news 
agency prensa latina reported thursday 
in charging bush with having a sick obsession about cuba 
castro cited what he said were a number of hostile acts by the 
united states against cuba 
he said the campaign included the initiation of voice of america 
television broadcasts to cuba and threatening military manuevers 
castro also criticized bush for asserting at the houston summit 
this month that the united states would withhold aid to the soviet 
union until kremlin economic and military aid to cuba is cut off 
citing the recent testimony of a cuban dissident castro accused 
the united states of instigating the wave of embassy breakins by 
asylumseekers on july 9 
the allegations were first aired a week ago and drew a flat 
denial from the us diplomatic mission here 
an official statement issued tuesday said no us official 
has ever encouraged or ever talked about cubans taking asylum in 
foreign embassies 
late thursday in washington the state department had no 
official reaction to castros remarks saying there likely would be 
a response friday after the speech is analyzed 
castro said the united states was also to blame for the 
situation at the embassies because it has not fulfilled a 1984 
agreement designed to facilitate cuban emigration to the united 
states us officials here said that 10000 visa applications from 
cubans had been processed since early 1988 it denied cuban charges 
that the united states has not fulfilled the agreement 
castro offered a daybyday account of the asylum issue some 
observers have speculated that hordes of cubans might seek shelter 
in embassies possibly destabilizing the regime which took power 
in 1959 
but the situation in the embassies appears to have stabilized in 
recent days there are 18 cubans being sheltered in the spanish 
embassy and four at the italian ambassadors residence 
three cubans who entered the swiss embassy last weekend departed 
voluntarily on wednesday 
castro normally makes his july 26 address in a provincial 
capital but decided this year to speak in havana the event marks 
the day in 1953 when castro led an attack on a military barracks in 
eastern cuba 
earlier thursday the state department in washington issued this 
statement on the anniversary 
tragically the revolutions promises with castros assumption 
of power in 1959 were betrayed there is little or no freedom of 
expression in cuba 
the regime has just announced that it will no longer permit 
the international committee of the red cross to visit cuban 
prisoners three decades after the revolution the cuban people are 
paying a high price for castros devotion to the discredited 
marxist model 
compared with the anniversary a year ago the mood in this 
caribbean island nation of about 105 million people off florida 
now is far more uncertain 
collapse of the friendly governments in eastern europe has 
brought an end to the socialist bloc grave uncertainty also has 
arisen about future economic ties with the soviet union cubas 
chief benefactor 
castro has warned his countrymen that harsh austerity measures 
will have to be imposed if the soviets stop sending 13 million tons 
of oil a year to cuba 
another concern is growing food scarcities many cubans say they 
cant recall when food supplies have been more meager 
for all his problems castros rule still is without serious 
challenge he continues to have a strong base of support and 
representatives of the small dissident community here are either in 
prison or have been cowed into silence 
</TEXT>
