following the deaths of five tigers within three months in the 
park at the time researchers in the park had just begun capturing 
tigers and putting radio collars around their necks to monitor 
their movements 
basavalingappa blamed the collars for the deaths but reports by 
the state ministry of forests and the central governments ministry 
of environment and forests concluded the deaths were unrelated to 
the project indeed only one of the five tigers had been collared 
