product safety commission and atv manufacturers has failed to 
adequately reduce the risk to consumers 
since the core problems is that children lack the 
developmental skills and maturity needed to operate any atv safely 
children must be kept off these vehicles said the consumer 
federation of america and the us public interest research group 
in a petition to be submitted to the commission 
in 1988 five atv manufacturers honda kawasaki suzuki 
yamaha and polaris agreed to ban sales of threewheel atvs in the 
united states for 10 years the consumer groups want a permanent 
ban on threewheelers 
the manufacturers also agreed to restrict sales of adultsize 
fourwheelers with engines 90 cubic centimeters or greater for use 
by people over 16 
our nationwide survey of atv dealers and a separate cpsc 
survey both found that atv dealers are willing to sell adultsize 
atvs to children added lucinda sikes an attorney with public 
interest research group 
surveys last year by that group and the commission found that 
more than half of atv dealers were ignoring the sales restrictions 
and adultsized vehicles could be obtained for young children 
however the agency said earlier this month that three of the 
manufacturers had further agreed to conduct routine dealer 
inspections and discipline dealers including termination of 
