communique which said the five have benefited from an act of 
clemency after having spent 10 years in prison they have been 
issued an order of expulsion from french territory which was 
carried out today 
naccache was one of three prisoners whose freedom was demanded 
by a group calling itself the committee for solidarity with arab 
and middle east prisoners which claimed responsibility for 
bombings in 198586 that killed 13 people and injured more than 250 
in paris 
