a truck driver whose rig careened into 
two cars at a construction site killing eight people blamed 
failed brakes for the fiery crash authorities said friday 
the driver manuel cruzado jr 25 of buffalo ny was 
charged with six counts of negligent homicide no further charges 
were planned until all the victims were identified 
cruzado who suffered minor burns told investigators his brakes 
failed 
the guy had passed three signs that there was a construction 
site one at a mile one at 1500 feet and one at 1000 feet and 
there was a big flashing arrow braxton county prosecutor william 
martin said 
frankly i think he could have avoided the wreck even if he 
didnt have brakes martin said at least he could have avoided 
hitting two carloads of people 
traffic was merging into one lane on interstate 79 on thursday 
evening near this central west virginia town when the 
tractortrailer rig loaded with eight cars came around a curve 
roared past a roadcrew flagman careened off the side of a bridge 
and struck two cars which burst into flames authorities said 
road crews tried to warn cruzado before the crash 
three of our people were trying to get the truckers 
attention flag him down he didnt see any of them said acting 
highways commissioner fred vankirk 
