<TEXT>
to fidel castro the spectacle of cubans fleeing 
his revolution is less a problem than an opportunity to score 
points against capitalist foes 
as is his custom castro went on the offensive thursday night 
daring the united states spain and other proponents of human 
rights to take in all cubans who are fed up with his revolution 
the only cubans exempted from this offer he said are the 40 or 
so who have barged into foreign embassies over the past 18 days to 
ask for political asylum 
it is inconsistent for western governments he said to offer 
refuge to unhappy cubans at their embassies on the one hand while 
not welcoming cubans who wish to emigrate through more conventional 
procedures 
in washington the bush administration sharply rejected castros 
sarcastic call for us ships to come and pick up cubans unhappy 
with his rule 
one of the darkest moments of castros 31year rule occurred 10 
years ago when 125000 cubans fled to florida aboard ships with 
little more than the shirts on their backs the exodus began when 
cubans by the thousands began seeking asylum at the peruvian 
embassy 
there was a sense of deja vu this month when cubans eager to 
leave began arriving at the czech embassy others sought refuge at 
embassies elsewhere in the capital 
could this be castros waterloo after all the communist regime 
in east germany began to unravel last year after hungary allowed 
east germans to escape to the west through its country within 
months democratic movements were sweeping communist governments 
from power throughout eastern europe 
castro easily survived the exodus a decade ago but now he is 
faced with political and ideological isolation and an economy worse 
off in many ways than it was in 1980 
when encountering difficulty castro is not one to pout he 
demonstrated that trait thursday night when he spoke to hundreds of 
thousands of his countrymen on the 37th anniversary of the start of 
his revolutionary movement 
he was especially tough on spain whose embassy has sheltered 18 
uninvited asylumseekers over the past week four others are at the 
italian ambassadors residence 
his voice rising in indignation castro chastized spain for 
sheltering cubans who were not targets of law enforcement 
authorities 
the spaniards he said are even giving refuge to a cuban who 
fought his way in with a machete 
he expressed outrage with spains decision last week to suspend 
