encouraging cubans to seek asylum at foreign embassies 
beyond that he said the united states has not fulfilled the 
1984 bilateral agreement on immigration thus indirectly forcing 
cubans who want to escape to utilize drastic means 
he also said bush was lobbying the soviet union to suspend aid 
to cuba and had threatened the island with military exercises in 
nearby waters 
when bush goes to eat breakfast he finds cuba in his coffee 
in the water in the bread castro said neither asleep nor 
awake does he forget about cuba it is a sick obsession and a shame 
for the world 
the us diplomatic mission here says the united states has 
lived up to the 1984 immigration agreement and never incited cubans 
to seek refuge at foreign embassies 
the spanish government said friday it had no interest in further 
conflict with cuba and did not encourage aslyumseekers 
accusatory or highflown phrases dont help very much to 
produce the dialogue needed to resolve the problem said the 
foreign ministry undersecretary inocencio arias 
