head down fractionally from last year and 1 percent below 1988 
the july 1 inventory of 1089 million head which includes 
calves and dairy cattle as well as beef stock included these 
categories compared with the last two years respectively 
beef cows 343 million up slightly from july 1 1989 and 1 
percent above july 1988 
milk cows 101 million unchanged from last year and 1 percent 
below two years ago 
all heifers 500 pounds and over 168 million up 1 percent 
from last year and up 2 percent from two years ago 
beef replacement heifers 52 million up 4 percent from 1989 
and 8 percent from 1988 
milk replacement heifers 43 million down 4 percent from last 
