zsa zsa gabor checked into the city 
jail friday to begin serving a threeday sentence for slapping a 
beverly hills motorcycle police officer 
the 72yearold celebrity dressed in slacks and a sweatshirt 
and clutching a goodluck frog appeared in good spirits when 
she checked in at 1 pm said fern ruiz a police department 
records clerk 
she seemed to be a very pleasant lady said ruiz 
after a threeweek highly publicized trial miss gabor was 
convicted of three misdemeanors sept 29 arising from her june 14 
1989 runin with officer paul kramer 
kramer who stopped miss gabors rollsroyce because its license 
plates had expired testified that miss gabor drove away from him 
when he pulled her over again she swore and slapped his face 
the actress who unsuccessfully appealed the 72hour jail 
sentence is to be released monday afternoon 
ruiz said miss gabor was the only prisoner at the 17person jail 
in this los angeles suburb when she checked in but that others 
were expected friday 
the onetime hungarian beauty queen will stay in an 8foot by 
10foot oneperson cell furnished with a metalframe bed a 
toilet and a sink ruiz said 
normally those who come in for these weekend stays just sit in 
their cells and if they want to work we usually have them do 
something like wash cars ruiz said 
in her case we didnt think that would be appropriate ruiz 
said so well have her doing the clerical work thats something 
she has expressed an interest in 
miss gabor will dine on tv dinners and be allowed to wear her 
own clothing like other jail prisoners ruiz said 
miss gabor is paying 85 a day to stay in the city jail of her 
choice otherwise she would have been assigned as a general 
population prisoner 
