<TEXT>
an aries rocket carrying 
a 20 million star wars experiment was destroyed shortly after 
liftoff because the rockets guidance system failed authorities 
said friday 
this will not significantly affect the program said lt 
col alan r freitag of the strategic defense initiative 
organization in washington its a very unfortunate loss 
certainly but not an insurmountable calamity 
the spear 2 experiment cost 20 million and the launch itself 
cost 1 million he said but the payload was designed to be 
recoverable so it will be difficult to calculate the loss 
the singlestage rocket was launched from white sands missile 
range at 1151 pm wednesday he said 
approximately 35 seconds into the mission flight safety 
determined that the missile was off course freitag said and the 
range missile flight safety officer decided to abort the launch by 
cutting off the rockets boost 
all pieces of the booster and the spear 2 experiment package 
fell within the boundaries of white sands missile range he said 
the payload was to have flown in a suborbital 13minute flight 
reaching an altitude of 124 miles freitag said 
maj bill oconnell of the star wars office in washington said 
the rocket had been scheduled to lift off a week ago but weather 
and other problems delayed the flight until wednesday 
spear 2 which stands for space power experiment aboard rocket 
was designed to provide scientific measurements of highvoltage 
conductors exposed to a space environment he said 
the experiment had undergone testing at the national aeronautics 
and space administrations plum brook space power facility at 
sandusky ohio he said 
the ground tests simulated experimental conditions in space 
freitag said 
but you can only have a certain degree of confidence that 
youve created the space environment on the ground he said 
the launch would have validated information already obtained at 
plum brook 
officials are considering the necessity of repeating the 
experiment in light of costs and the scientific data already 
obtained through ground testing he said 
the senate last month trimmed 1 billion from president bushs 
47 billion budget request for sdi a research effort to develop 
lasers and other exotic weapons that could shoot down nuclear 
missiles fired at the united states 
</TEXT>
