networks strategy or to say whether nbc would implement its last 
contract offer when the company did that in 1987 the union began 
its long strike 
nbcs offer provides for a 3 percent pay hike upon ratification 
and would not be retroactive salaries would rise another 3 percent 
in the contracts second year union members would get a lumpsum 
payment equal to 5 percent of their base salary in the third year 
and a 4 percent raise in the contracts last year 
krieger said money was not a major issue the main issues 
include jurisdiction daily hires and fourwalling proposals 
he said 
