john henry knapp freed three years ago after 
spending 12 years on death row for allegedly setting fire to his 
trailer with his two young daughters inside was charged again 
thursday in their deaths 
the charges came in a barebones twopage complaint and the 
state attorney generals office refused to say what new evidence it 
might have 
prosecutors claim that knapp now 44 set the nov 16 1973 fire 
that killed linda louise and iona marie knapp ages 2 and 3 while 
they slept in the family house trailer in suburban mesa 
knapps attorneys claim the fire was started either by knapps 
thenwife linda or by the children themselves 
knapp was sentenced to death in january 1975 but was freed in 
1987 by maricopa county superior court judge stephen gerst who 
ruled that new defense evidence left it unclear what or who started 
the fire 
the new charges come weeks before an election for attorney 
general and knapps attorney mark wallace said the timing seemed 
curious 
the facts speak themselves he said i think you should 
draw your own conclusions 
a spokesman for the prosecutors office cathy czagany said 
prosecutors would not discuss their evidence for fear of violating 
courtimposed rules on what lawyers may say before trial 
knapp has been living with relatives in texas and pennsylvania 
since being released he was arrested on the new charges wednesday 
night in carnegie pa and is being held without bond pending 
extradition 
knapp then a taxi driver admitted his guilt shortly after the 
fire but retracted his statement he has since maintained that he 
gave the statement because of pain from recurring migraine 
headaches 
the states expert had claimed the fire was so fast and fierce 
that it must have been fed by flammable material but knapps 
lawyers said their expert believed the trailers carpet could have 
been set alight by children playing with matches and still produced 
the same burn pattern that the states expert claimed was proof of 
an accelerant 
