<TEXT>
roger welsch loves stories 
he writes them on bar napkins he tells them with great skill 
he remembers them even if he forgets almost everything else 
i cant remember your name he said recently with some 
embarrassment but if you told me a story right now i would 
remember the story 
welschs stories which deal with the humor and wisdom found in 
smalltown america are featured on sunday morning the cbs 
program hosted by charles kuralt his twoyear contract was 
recently renewed and viewers are assured of at least eight of 
welschs postcards from nebraska each year 
before cbs he taught folklore and literature not your typical 
buttoneddown academician he sported a long ponytail with a 
feather tied in it eventually he left his tenured position at the 
university of nebraskalincoln for life in this village of 380 
people 
that decision came slowly and with some fear welsch said hed 
worked for tenure all his life he was married and had a daughter 
but he had purchased 60 acres and he wanted his child antonia 
to grow up in the country he also needed the open spaces and 
quieter lifestyle 
i loved the people and the river and the land said welsch 
53 it was time to move 
welsch moved to dannebrog from lincoln in 1987 when he took a 
leave of absence he resigned his teaching position the next year 
he hoped to earn a living speaking at banquets writing for 
magazines and a weekly column for 13 nebraska newspapers but the 
ends werent meeting 
i told my wife linda ive got bad news and ive got worse 
news welsch recalled the bad news is were not making it 
the worse news is im not going back 
about two months later fortune and charles kuralt stepped in 
welsch had done several pieces over the years for kuralts show 
the avuncular newsman was sitting in the audience one night as 
welsch spoke at a west point chamber of commerce banquet 
he came very quietly in the back of the room and asked if 
welsch would like to join the show 
the program gave welsch the financial security he needed 
it also made him a tv star and made this central nebraska town 
on the edge of the semiarid sandhills famous around the country 
many in this town with one main street one bar a restaurant a 
drivein and two gas stations enjoy the newfound fame others 
dont 
hes just a big blowhard said charles fox 75 whose wife 
lucile runs an antique store in town 
fox said some people who travel to dannebrog are disappointed 
there isnt more to see fox also said he was described in one of 
welschs articles as the surliest and cheapest guy in howard 
