threeyear contract wasnt approved by next tuesday when the old 
pact expires ups spokesman ken sternad said thursday 
but he said the union needed more time to get all its members to 
vote on the proposal the new deadline for ratifying a contract was 
set at aug 10 
ups has about 150000 parttime and fulltime employees who are 
teamsters members the company employs 230000 workers and is the 
worlds largest package delivery service it made 28 billion 
deliveries last year and had 124 billion in revenue 
the union told ups it had problems getting ballots to many of 
its members and needed extra time to get them back sternad said 
the company said its contract proposal calls for higher wages 
improved benefits and better working conditions 
the proposed contract would raise wages for the average ups 
fulltime driver to 18 an hour within two years sternad said ups 
drivers now make an average of 1610 per hour 
parttime workers mostly package handlers and truck loaders 
currently start at 8 or 9 an hour under the proposed contract 
their wages would increase 150 an hour sternad said 
company contributions for health benefits and employees 
pensions currently at 8300 a year for fulltime workers would 
increase to 10500 by the end of the three years he said for 
parttime workers the rate would increase by 105 an hour 
the proposal also offers a onetime bonus of 1000 to 
fulltimers and 500 to parttimers to be paid within the first 
month after ratification he said 
the company has agreed to make the contract retroactive to aug 
1 if it is ratified sternad said 
</TEXT>
