members exceeding their output quotas it said kuwait and the 
united arab emirates largely were responsible for the current glut 
oil traders had been predicting opec would take action to curb 
production and that anticipation helped sharply boost wholesale 
prices in recent weeks 
for instance since june 1 crude oil futures have risen about 
3 a barrel unleaded gasoline about 14 cents and home heating 
oil around 10 cents according to energy experts 
james steel an energy analyst with refco inc in new york said 
the general rule of thumb is that every dollar rise in a barrel of 
crude oil means a nickel rise at the pumps 
he said that if the opec agreement pushes crude up 350 to 4 a 
barrel as some expect will happen by december we could see an 
increase of between 15 cents and 20 cents in early 1991 
