<TEXT>
bond prices climbed friday on further signs of 
weak economic growth 
the treasurys benchmark 30year bond gained 1116 point or 
688 per 1000 in face amount its yield which falls when prices 
rise dropped to 847 percent from 854 percent late thursday 
the spurt came after the commerce department said the gross 
national product the countrys total output of goods and services 
grew at an annual rate of just 12 percent from april through june 
economists said the report gave further impetus to a belief the 
economy is sliding into a recession 
additionally gnp secondquarter increase followed a revised 17 
percent increase in the first quarter and a barely discernible 03 
percent advance in the octoberdecember period last year 
slower growth increases the likelihood that inflation will be 
mild which increases the value of fixedincome investments such as 
treasury bonds 
kevin flanagan money market economist for dean witter reynolds 
inc said the rise in bond prices was restrained partly by an 
inflation measure in the gnp report that was higher than expected 
inflation erodes the value of bonds 
also some economists tempered their enthusiasm for the gnp 
number arguing it was weaker than it would be after government 
revisions in coming months 
mike casey an international economist with ramirez capital 
consultants inc said the gnp number was not bad enough to force 
the federal reserve to lower interest rates to spur the economy 
which would push bond prices higher 
trading activity was moderate 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
governments gained about point intermediate maturities rose 932 
point to 716 point and longterm issues were up as much as 1116 
point according to telerate inc a financial information service 
the movement of a point is equivalent to a change of 10 in the 
price of a bond with a 1000 face value 
the shearson lehman hutton daily treasury bond index which 
measures price movements on all outstanding treasury issues with 
maturities of a year or longer was 429 higher at 116431 
yields on threemonth treasury bills fell to 777 percent as the 
discount was down 4 basis points to 753 percent yields on 
sixmonth bills dropped to 779 percent as the discount declined 5 
basis points to 741 percent yields on oneyear bills fell to 779 
percent from thursdays auction as the discount tumbled 7 basis 
points to 727 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
the federal funds rate the interest banks charge each other on 
overnight loans was quoted at 8 percent unchanged from late 
thursday 
in the taxexempt market the bond buyer index of 40 actively 
traded municipal bonds was 92 up 732 point the average yield to 
maturity fell to 737 percent down from 739 percent late thursday 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

