<TEXT>
montedison spa and ferruzzi agricola 
finanziaria spa announced plans on friday to merge into a holding 
company that would combine all the chemical and agroindustrial 
interests of italys ferruzzi group 
the new company to be named montedison spa will have annual 
aggregate sales of 35 trillion lire or about 30 billion 
state television said the operation would put the italian group 
on footing with such european giants as bayer 
raul gardini chairman of ferruzzi finanziaria spa the key 
financial holding of the ferruzzi group told a news conference 
that the merger aimed to create a global company designed to face 
the challenges of the 1990s and capable of pursuing an 
evergrowing integration between the chemicals and 
agroindustrial businesses 
currently ferruzzi finanziaria owns 668 percent of ferruzzi 
agricola which in turn holds 487 percent of montedison a large 
part of montedisons chemical interests are concentrated in enimont 
spa a 40 percentowned joint venture with stateowned energy 
company ente nazionale idrocarburi eni 
ferruzzi agricola also owns 53 percent of eridania spa which 
combines the groups agroindustrial interests 
shareholders of both montedison and ferruzzi agricola will be 
asked to approve the merger plan at assemblies in early november 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

