<DOCNO> AP900727-0240 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a year after shelving plans to build a new 
ethylene plant at its chocolate bayou facility amoco corp 
announced it will spend 200 million to expand its existing 
ethylene production plant 
the expansion scheduled to be completed by nearly 1994 would 
boost the companys ethylene production by 600 million pounds per 
year 
the alvin texas plant which employs 824 already is capable 
of producing 24 billion pounds of ethylene per year and 800 
million pounds of propylene 
ethylene and propylene are used in making plastics industrial 
chemicals and a variety of consumer products 
at amoco much of the ethylene produced at chocolate bayou is 
used by the companys fabrics and fibers business which makes 
carpet backing fibers and yarns 
a year ago amoco shelved plans to build a 15 
billionpoundayear ethylene plant at the time both the company 
and outside observers were predicting a glut of the chemical by 
1993 and an accompanying fall in prices 
still amoco officials say their projections show ethylene 
demand will remain healthy enough to support the new capacity 
</TEXT>
